               <head>Treatise on Sufism, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous fragments, substantially comprised of an unidentified work on Sufism. 
Volume not dated; item b dated ([1] Ṣafar 1096/[7] January 1685). 
Annotations in margins. 
Lacking foliation. 
Lacking original binding.
Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on the trade of tobacco and ganza, dated 30 January 1852); watermarked (crowned lion rampant guardant, in crowned oval frame; not dated); labels, torn and stained. 
Folios unbound; large wormholes, stains, creases. 
Condition fragile. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_79x-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="1v">ff. 1r-1v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 79* a. 
</p>
                        <p>Detached sheet of accounts relating to the repair of Rampur fort. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Raqm annotations. </p>
                     </note>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_79x-item2">
                     <locus from="2r" to="103r">ff. 2r-103r </locus>
                     <author/>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 79* b. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Sufism by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is defective at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacunae after folio 7. 
</p>
                        <p>It is quite possible that folios 2-7 are later replacement folios augmenting an older fragmentary copy. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 103r): completed by Sayyid Aʿẓam Ḥusaynī for Miyān Shaykh Muḥammad Fāz̤il, midday Sunday, [1] Ṣafar 1096/[7] January 1685, in the reign of Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I. 
</p>
                        <p>Inelegant scribal nastaʿlīq frequently tending to shikastah āmīz by multiple hands. 
</p>
                        <p>Ends with a rough and incomplete transcription of sūrah Fātiḥah (<title key="work_22251">Qurʾān</title>, I: 1-3) by a later hand. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
